Canadians have indicated that they want to see greater protection of their national heritage. 
We have a responsibility to ensure that protection is afforded before it is too late.  
Mr. John Duncan (Vancouver Island North, Ref.):
Mr. Speaker, I am happy to speak to Bill C-236, an act to amend the National Parks Act. 
It specifically deals with the Elaho Valley near Squamish.  
In the case of this private member's bill from the member for Davenport, the Liberal government is on the record as not being in favour of it. 
